These scenarios will be accessible to all test cases in the the FitNesseRoot folder. If you are using a different FitNesseRoot Folder, make sure to copy these files if using any setup scenarios.


Update these variables for your specific test environment

Variables for Scenarios

Default browser can be FIREFOX or CHROME
variable defined: defaultBrowser=FIREFOX

Default Version can be any supported Appian Version in xx.x format from (21.2 - 23.1)
variable defined: defaultVersion=23.1

Default Locale can be en_US or en_GB
variable defined: defaultLocale=en_US

Default URL should include http or https and /suite (e.g. https://forum.appian.com/suite )
variable defined: defaultUrl=REPLACE_APPIAN_URL

To use out of the box functionality, do not update the scenarios below

FitNesse Configurations


variable defined: TEST_SYSTEM=slim
variable defined: COMMAND_PATTERN=java -Dlog4j.configuration=file:///${automated.testing.home}/log4j.properties -cp %p %m
classpath: C:\FitNesse/**.jar
variable defined: Name=Vijay Kumar
variable defined: ContactType=Client

Please follow the directions below to execute the test


  1. If your TESTING_HOME is located somewhere other than C:\FitNesse, update automated.testing.home in TESTING_HOME/configs/custom.properties
    • For more information look at Changing FitNesse for Appian installation directory.
  2. Click "Edit" at the top of this page and update the following fields in the "Initialization and Login" block below
    • Replace APPIAN_URL with Appian URL, beginning with https:// and including /suite at the end (e.g. https://forum.appian.com/suite)
    • Replace APPIAN_VERSION with a supported version from (21.2 - 23.1)
    • Replace APPIAN_LOCALE with (en_US or en_GB) to handle differences in how dates are displayed
    • Replace APPIAN_USERNAME with a valid username for Appian URL above
    • Open C:\FitNesse/configs/users.properties and add a line for the above username that is of the form username=password (e.g. test.user=password)
  3. Click "Test" at the top of this page
